From #5177 (unrelated to that bug's real problem):

```
import "DPI-C" function string getenvval(input string env_name);
string       RISCV_DIR = getenvval("RISCV");

const char *getenvval(const char *pszName) {
    return ((const char *) getenv(pszName));
}
```

When RISCV is not defined this returns null. @davidharrishmc you should ask to get the C code fixed - have it return e.g. "" or give an error or whatever.

But, to defend against crashes Verilator should treat nulls as "" when dpi-importing a null string.
